## Missing Nested Object

```js
const user = {
    name: "Umar"
};

console.log(user.address?.city);
```

### Output

```txt
undefined
```

---

# Deep Optional Chaining

```js
const user = {
    address: {
        location: {
            city: "Agra"
        }
    }
};

console.log(user?.address?.location?.city);
```

### Output

```txt
Agra
```

---

# Comparison

## Without Optional Chaining

```js
if(
    user &&
    user.address &&
    user.address.location &&
    user.address.location.city
){
    console.log(user.address.location.city);
}
```

---

## With Optional Chaining

```js
console.log(user?.address?.location?.city);
```

Same result, much cleaner code.

---

# Arrays

```js
const products = [
    { name: "Bag" }
];

console.log(products?.[0]?.name);
```

### Output

```txt
Bag
```

---

# Functions

```js
const user = {
    sayHello() {
        console.log("Hello");
    }
};

user.sayHello?.();
```

### Output

```txt
Hello
```

If function doesn't exist:

```js
user.sayBye?.();
```

Output:

```txt
undefined
```

No error.

