# MongoDB / Mongoose Example

```js
console.log(product.image?.data);
console.log(product.image?.contentType);
```

Useful when some documents have images and some do not.

Example:

```js
{
    name: "Nike Bag",
    image: {
        data: Buffer(...),
        contentType: "image/png"
    }
}
```

and

```js
{
    name: "Adidas Bag"
}
```

Optional chaining prevents runtime errors.

---

# Best Practice

Use optional chaining whenever:

* API response may contain missing fields.
* MongoDB documents may have optional properties.
* Nested objects may not exist.
* Working with user-generated data.

Examples:

```js
user?.profile?.avatar
```

```js
product?.image?.data
```

```js
req.user?.email
```

```js
response?.data?.users
```

---

# Key Rule

`?.` means:

> "Agar left side exist karti hai to aage jao, warna `undefined` return kar do aur error mat do."

Example:

```js
user?.address?.city
```

Equivalent to:

```js
if(user && user.address){
    return user.address.city;
}
```

Optional Chaining = Cleaner Code + Fewer Errors 🚀
